    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>i don&#8217;t consider this a problem. think of it this way: that you have found your holy grail banana cake recipe, or you have found the absolute lemon cupcake recipe. why try anything else? you&#8217;ve reached the pinnacle, the search for absoluteness, for prefection is over. so that when you want a banana cake, or a lemon cupcake (or whatever) you can reach with confidence for the one recipe that will satisfy you. and then that dish becomes your faithful &#8212; indeed, your signature dish that you are loyal to. i think there is nothign wrong with approaching certain dishes like this!</p>
